{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/153/comments/90520937.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/diff/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo:afcbbaecfb96..33fa6f76252f?path=src%2Fsystems%2Fusercommands%2FUserCommands.cc"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/153/_/diff#comment-90520937"}}, "parent": {"id": 90514671, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/153/comments/90514671.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/153/_/diff#comment-90514671"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 153, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pullrequests/153.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-gazebo/pull-requests/153"}}, "title": "[A-6] User command: Delete / remove / erase"}, "content": {"raw": "`components::Model` is  just a `TagWrapper`, while `components::Light` is a `SimpleWrapper` around an `sdf::Light`. This makes `components::Light` hard to use with `EntityByComponents`, because we'd have to compare the SDF objects. I think we could revisit this eventually and have 2 separate components, or alternatively, have a way to get entities that have components by type, but not by content.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p><code>components::Model</code> is  just a <code>TagWrapper</code>, while <code>components::Light</code> is a <code>SimpleWrapper</code> around an <code>sdf::Light</code>. This makes <code>components::Light</code> hard to use with <code>EntityByComponents</code>, because we'd have to compare the SDF objects. I think we could revisit this eventually and have 2 separate components, or alternatively, have a way to get entities that have components by type, but not by content.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-02-05T18:13:23.693755+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Louise Poube